obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4855  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 6:\"cLTD treatment induced a significant decrease in GluA1 intensity within the synaptic areas both upon EGFP and Rabaptin-5 wt overexpression but not in Rabaptin-5 S407A expressing neurons (Figure 6A,B). Our data thus provide evidence that phosphorylation of Rabaptin-5 at serine 407 regulates basal and activity-induced AMPAR endocytosis most probably downstream of PKD.\"\n\nAuthor summary of presented data; \"PKD is activated downstream of NMDA and AMPA receptor signaling and promotes AMPAR endocytosis probably via regulating Rab5 activity through Rabaptin-5\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary cultures of embryonic hippocampal cells were prepared from CD1 mice on embryonic day E17.5-E18.5.\"\n\n\"EGFP-Rabaptin-5 wild type and EGFP-Rabaptin-5 S407A25 were kindly provided by Alex Toker, Beth Israel Deaconess Center, Harvard Medical School.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4855" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

